.SH NAME
set_primary_fwnode \- Change the primary firmware node of a given device.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" set_primary_fwnode
.BI "(struct device *dev "  ","
.BI "struct fwnode_handle *fwnode "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
Device to handle.
.IP "fwnode" 12
New primary firmware node of the device.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Set the device's firmware node pointer to \fIfwnode\fP, but if a secondary
firmware node of the device is present, preserve it.

Valid fwnode cases are:
- primary --> secondary --> -ENODEV
- primary --> NULL
- secondary --> -ENODEV
- NULL
